window.globalProvideData('caption', '{"data":"WEBVTT%0D%0AKind:%20captions%0D%0ASource:%20Articulate%20Closed%20Captions%20Editor%0D%0ASource%20Version:%206.20.16814.0%0D%0A%0D%0A00:00:00.001%20--%3E%2000:00:03.580%0D%0ANow,%20take%20the%20first%20overtape.%20%0D%0A%0D%0A00:00:03.649%20--%3E%2000:00:06.952%0D%0AYou%20use%20the%20overtape%20to%20make%20sure%20the%20sensor%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20fall%20off.%0D%0A%0D%0A00:00:07.009%20--%3E%2000:00:11.008%0D%0ARemove%20the%20large%20paper%20backing%20from%20the%20overtape,%20but%20not%20the%20two%20smaller%20ones%20on%20the%20sides.%20%0D%0A%0D%0A00:00:11.209%20--%3E%2000:00:20.493%0D%0AOn%20one%20side,%20place%20the%20overtape%20on%20the%20sensor%20itself,%20%0D%0A%0D%0A00:00:20.494%20--%3E%2000:00:27.044%0D%0Aand%20put%20the%20other%20side%20under%20the%20connector.%20%0D%0A%0D%0A00:00:27.045%20--%3E%2000:00:36.564%0D%0AThen,%20remove%20the%20small%20paper%20liners%20and%20make%20the%20remaining%20overtape%20stick%20to%20your%20skin.%0D%0A%0D%0A"}')